Enum Form

java.lang.Object
  java.lang.Enum<Form>
      simplenlg.features.Form
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Comparable<Form>
public enum Form
extends Enum<Form>

The form of the verb (and its associated sentence). Cases distinguished:

  • NORMAL: any form except the following:
  • INFINITIVE: To eat an apple.
  • GERUND: Eating an apple.
  • IMPERATIVE: Eat an apple.

Author:
agatt

hasSubject

public boolean hasSubject()
Returns:
true if a sentence in this form can have a subject. This is in fact only true for the NORMAL case.

isEmbedded

public boolean isEmbedded()
Check if a sentence in this form can be embedded within another sentence. This is in fact only allowed for the values INFINITIVE and GERUND. Examples:
  • (INFINITIVE) To eat an apple is dangerous.
  • (GERUND) Eating an apple is dangerous.

Returns:
true if a sentence in this form can be embedded.

allowsTense

public boolean allowsTense()
* check if this form allows tenses (past, future)

isCompatible

public boolean isCompatible(Mood m)
Tests the compatibility of a given Form with a given Mood. In particular, you cannot have a GERUND or INFINITIVE form for a clause if the clause is a SUBJUNCTIVE, COMMAND (imperative) or a QUESTION.

Parameters:
m - A value of Mood
Returns:
true if this mood and this form are compatible.
